# BePlus Smart Search — front-end (JS + CSS)

## Source vs build

| Edit | Output |
|------|--------|
| `admin/js/**` | `build/admin.js`, `build/admin.css`, `build/admin.asset.php` |
| `assets/js/**`, `assets/css/**` | `build/frontend.js` (if configured) |
| `blocks/<name>/block.js` | `build/blocks/<name>.js` via wp-scripts |

Run **`npm run build`** or **`npm run start`** after source changes. Never hand-edit `build/**`.

## Admin (React)

- Entry: `admin/js/admin.js` — settings dashboard, analytics, provider toggles.
- Use `@wordpress/*` packages; read dependencies from `build/admin.asset.php`.
- REST calls target `beplus-smart-search/v1`; pass `X-WP-Nonce` from localized `bpssData.nonce`.

## Front-end (search UI)

- Autocomplete / live search: fetch `rest_url( 'beplus-smart-search/v1/search' )`.
- Localized data shape:

```php
array(
  'restUrl' => rest_url( 'beplus-smart-search/v1/' ),
  'nonce'   => wp_create_nonce( 'wp_rest' ),
)
```

- CSS prefix: `beplus-smart-search` with BEM (`__element--modifier`).
- Keep plugin styles scoped — do not reset global theme styles.

## Block editor scripts

- Block category: `beplus-smart-search`.
- Block name prefix: `beplus-smart-search/`.
- `@wordpress/*` externals map to `window.wp.*` in built output.

```text
❌ Hard-code /wp-json/ path in admin/js/api.js
✅ Use bpssData.restUrl from wp_localize_script

❌ Global .button { … } in assets/css/frontend.css
✅ .beplus-smart-search__submit { … }
```
